"'''Down'''" is a song by British rock band [[The Kooks]]. It was released on 18 April 2014 through [[Virgin EMI Records]]<ref name="Virgin digital"/> as the [[lead single]] from the band's upcoming fourth studio album ''[[Listen (The Kooks album)|Listen]]'', which was scheduled to be released on 1 September 2014.<ref name="NME Listen">{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/the-kooks/76889 |title=The Kooks announce new album 'Listen' |work=[[NME]] |date=24 April 2014 |accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref> The song debuted on [[UK Singles Chart]] at number 40.<ref name="UKchart"/> It has also reportedly divided fans.<ref name="Clash">{{cite web|url=http://www.clashmusic.com/news/listen-the-kooks-down |title=Listen: The Kooks - Down |work=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]] |first=Robin |last=Murray |date=12 April 2014 |accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>

==Background and release==
"Down" is the first song released by The Kooks since their 2012 single "Rosie". The song was written by the band's frontman Luke Pritchard and hip-hop pioneer Inflo for the band's upcoming studio album ''[[Listen (The Kooks album)|Listen]]''.<ref name="ContactMusic">{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/press/the-kooks-return-with-new-single-down-available-april-20-listen |title=The Kooks Return With New Single 'Down,' Available April 20 [Listen] |publisher=[[Contactmusic.com]] |accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref> "Down" was recorded in [[Los Angeles]] and [[London]].<ref name="Clash"/> According to reports, the song is "a mission statement from a band that have rediscovered what they loved about making music in the first place." The [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]-inspired track features "looped hooks and crazy percussion" and has a "contagious swagger."<ref name="ContactMusic"/><ref name="NME">{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/the-kooks/76030 |title=The Kooks unveil R&B-inspired new single 'Down' – listen |work=[[NME]] |date=12 March 2014 |accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>

The song premiered on 11 March 2014 on [[BBC Radio 1]] as [[Zane Lowe]]'s 'Hottest Record'.<ref name="Clash"/><ref name="ContactMusic"/> It was released digitally on 18 April 2014,<ref name="Virgin digital"/> and as a [[7" vinyl]] on 21 April 2014.<ref name="Virgin 7"/>

==Music video==
A music video for the song was released onto [[YouTube]] on 20 March 2014.<ref name="YouTube">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p2tjsNabkzo |title=The Kooks - Down |publisher=[[YouTube]] |date=20 March 2014 |accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref> It was directed by Davis Silis.<ref name="Digital Spy">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a559361/the-kooks-unveil-video-for-new-single-down-watch.html |title=The Kooks unveil video for new single 'Down' - watch |first=Tom |last=Eames |publisher=[[Digital Spy]] |date=21 March 2014 |accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>

